      <hr />
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="conventions">
        <div>
            <p><strong>Qualifying Information - </strong>In displays, qualifying information may be enclosed in parentheses.</p>
         </div>
         <div>
            <p><strong>Structure - </strong>Other Standard Identifiers are unique, permanent and internationally recognized
               alphanumeric codes used to identify entities. The codes may be defined by
               the ISO (International Organization for Standardization) and assigned by designated
               agencies. Some examples of these identifiers include the ISTC (International Standard
               Text Code), the ISWC (International Standard Musical Work Code), and the ISAN
               (International Standard Audiovisual Number). The structure of these numbers is
               determined by the agencies formulating them.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
